
//docker volume create testthing
it will creates a new volume "testthing" that containers can consume and store data in.

//docker run --name=testthing alpine date
it will outputs the date and time of alpine image

//docker inspect testthing
It will provide the whole data of testthing

// From this command " docker inspect [OPTIONS] NAME|ID [NAME|ID...]" we can inspect exactly what we want.
like in this case "docker inspect type=container testthing